`crates/ctx-scan/src` is the whole `ctx-scan` binary+lib: a standalone tool (git-independent) that walks a directory, maintains a `.context/` mirror of hash-tracked summaries, and exposes scan/check/update/prune/stop-hook modes both as a CLI and as a library other tools can call. Depending on this crate gets you content-hash-based staleness detection and mirror reconciliation without any model calls unless regeneration is actually needed.

The core data flow: `walker::walk_dir` produces the scoped file list (respecting `.ctxignore`, always excluding `.context`/`.git`, secrets/binaries) → `hash::compute`/`diff` turns that into a `Staleness` report → `reconcile` finds/prunes orphaned mirror artifacts not in the walker's target set → `runner` orchestrates these plus `ctx-summarize`'s model calls into the four public entry points (`scan_run`/`check_run`/`prune_run`/`update_run`) → `cli`/`main` dispatch CLI args to those, and `render` formats the results as line-oriented (non-parseable) text. `staleness.rs`'s `Staleness` struct is the shared contract threaded through hash, reconcile, runner, render, and cli's stop-hook path — its five fields and the `is_fresh`/`needs_regeneration` distinction must stay consistent across all of them, since orphan-detection logic is duplicated between `check_run` and `update_run`'s staleness computation.

Two cross-cutting invariants worth knowing before editing: (1) `.context` mirror layout (`cpath::context_dir_of`/`ancestor_dirs`) must match how `ctx-summarize` writes leaves/rollups — hash.rs and reconcile.rs both assume this; (2) prompts are always resolved against process cwd, never the scan target `base`, in both `cli.rs` and `runner.rs` — a common footgun. Adding a new CLI mode requires updating `cli.rs` dispatch/exclusivity, a matching `runner::*_run`, and possibly `contract.rs`'s `CONTRACT` string (checked against README/CLAUDE.md by a test). Stop-hook and all agent-free modes are fail-open/fail-fast respectively and never construct a `SubprocessAgent`, keeping them usable without API keys.